author: jgomes
msg: Call the exceptionHandler in Oneway() instead of throwing an exception if the connection is closed.  This is more consistent behavior.

Protect access to the closed variable in Close() using the myLock critical section lock.  Even though closed is an Atomic boolean, that code block should be protected by the critical section lock for consistency.
All passing unit tests continue to pass with these changes.
